ordinator — all fixed with new tests\n    22→- **MEDIUM: formatAuditJson did pointless property copy** — simplified to direct return\n    23→- **LOW (not fixed): report.ts dead-code fallback `?? '[WARN]'`** — impossible to reach with typed DimensionStatus\n    24→- **LOW (not fixed): readdirSafe uses `as string[]` cast** — fragile if someone adds withFileTypes option\n    25→- **Architecture: checkVerification hardcodes sprint-status.yaml path** — should be configurable but not blocking\n    26→- **Coverage: 96.71% overall, all 116 files above 80% floor, 2779 tests pass**\n    27→\n    28→### 3-2-audit-fix-story-generation — create-story (2026-03-20T09:14Z)\n    29→\n    30→- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n    31→- **Expanded ACs from 3 to 10:** Original epic definition had only 3 sparse ACs. Agent expanded to cover edge cases, JSON output, idempotency, atomic writes, and precondition checks.\n    32→- **Risk: Story key collision.** The `audit-fix-{dimension}-{index}` key scheme uses sequential index. If gaps change between runs, same index could map to different gaps. Content-based hash would be more robust.\n    33→- **Risk: sprint-state.json vs sprint-status.yaml divergence.** Epic says stories go to sprint-state.json, but sprint planning also uses sprint-status.yaml. Generated stories won't appear in sprint-status.yaml unless manually synced.\n    34→\n    35→### 3-2-audit-fix-story-generation — dev-story (2026-03-20T09:19Z)\n    36→\n    37→- **Test file exceeds NFR9:** `fix-generator.test.ts` is 426 lines (estimated 200-250). Thorough AC coverage with mocking requires more code. Test files generally exempt from NFR9.\n    38→- **Type gymnastics in audit.ts:** Uses `ReturnType<typeof generateFixStories>` pattern to avoid importing internal Result type. Works but not cleanest.\n    39→- **No end-to-end verification:** Task 7.5 requires `codeharness audit --fix` against a real initialized project — only unit tests cover the paths. E2E test deferred to review.\n    40→- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n    41→\n    42→### 3-2-audit-fix-story-generation — code-review (2026-03-20T09:24Z)\n    43→\n    44→- **HIGH: Error path in fix-generator.ts catch block untested (lines 117-120)** — FIXED with 2 new tests.\n    45→- **MEDIUM: JSON output silently swallowed errors** from generateFixStories() and addFixStoriesToState() in --fix --json mode — FIXED with fixError/fixStateError fields.\n    46→- **MEDIUM: Complex type annotation in audit.ts** — replaced ugly ReturnType inference with clean Result<FixGenerationResult> import.\n    47→- **HIGH: AGENTS.md stale** — missing fix-types.ts and fix-generator.ts entries — FIXED.\n    48→- **LOW (not fixed): fix-types.ts shows 0% coverage** — types-only file, cosmetic artifact.\n    49→- **LOW (not fixed): double-cast in audit.ts line 92** — formatAuditJson return type needs better upstream definition.\n    50→- **Architecture: Story key positional dependency** — index-based scheme shifts when gaps change. Acceptable for current scope.\n    51→- **Coverage: 96.72% overall, all 118 files above 80% floor, 2812 tests pass**\n    52→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c9a200e-72ec-477b-8ec4-6d2e01a30422","uuid":"8d733e71-34f4-4567-880c-9297a6edd414","timestamp":"2026-03-21T04:22:23.462Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 11)\n\n### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — create-story (2026-03-20T08:39Z)\n\n- **No integration-required ACs:** All 7 ACs are cli-verifiable. Runtime observability dimension internally depends on backend, but AC tests graceful degradation path.\n- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n- **Risk: Infrastructure dimension underspecified.** Story 4.1 defines full