tes call this out but it needs verification during implementation.\n- The old onboard command has `epic` subcommand functionality (interactive approval, beads import, sprint-status append) that has no equivalent in audit. Dropping this silently may surprise users who relied on `codeharness onboard epic`.\n\n**Observations:**\n- The old `onboard.ts` is 478 lines — the rewrite should reduce it to ~40-60 lines, a significant simplification.\n- The epic's AC3 (\"onboard scan maps to equivalent audit subcommand\") is somewhat ambiguous since audit has no direct scan subcommand. The story interprets this as a deprecation path."}],"totalDurationMs":133439,"totalTokens":48622,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3827,"cache_read_input_tokens":44143,"output_tokens":651,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3827},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
