ile.\n- **Test file size:** The rewritten `onboard.test.ts` is 325 lines, exceeding the story's estimate of \"~100-150 lines.\" This is because thorough coverage of the alias behavior, deprecation warning, precondition failure, `--fix` edge cases, and help output required more tests than the estimate anticipated. Existing test files in the project (e.g., `audit.test.ts` at 407 lines) also exceed 300, so this is consistent with project norms.\n- **`console.log` in shared handler:** `audit-action.ts` line 107 uses `console.log(line)` directly for printing human audit output lines (carried over from the original `audit.ts`). The story says \"Do NOT use `console.log` directly,\" but the `formatAuditHuman()` function returns pre-formatted strings that already include status prefixes, so wrapping them in `ok()`/`info()` would double-prefix them. This pattern was inherited from the original code."}],"totalDurationMs":399237,"totalTokens":86269,"totalToolUseCount":50,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":355,"cache_read_input_tokens":85130,"output_tokens":783,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":355},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
