{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012txaQqg7PUd8znZrg37URe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Proof: 3-3 Onboard Alias\n     2→\n     3→## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n     4→\n     5→### AC #1: `codeharness onboard` produces identical output to `codeharness audit`\n     6→- **Verified:** Both commands call `executeAudit({ isJson, isFix })` from the same shared handler (`audit-action.ts`). Code path is identical.\n     7→- **Test:** `onboard.test.ts` — \"delegates to audit logic when run with no flags\"\n     8→\n     9→### AC #2: `codeharness onboard --fix` produces identical output to `codeharness audit --fix`\n    10→- **Verified:** `--fix` flag is mirrored and passed to `executeAudit()`.\n    11→- **Test:** `onboard.test.ts` — \"delegates to audit --fix logic\"\n    12→\n    13→### AC #3: `codeharness onboard --json` produces identical JSON to `codeharness audit --json`\n    14→- **Verified:** `--json` flag is mirrored and passed to `executeAudit()`.\n    15→- **Test:** `onboard.test.ts` — \"produces same JSON output as audit --json\"\n    16→\n    17→### AC #4: `codeharness onboard --fix --json` produces identical output\n    18→- **Verified:** Both flags passed through to shared handler.\n    19→- **Test:** `onboard.test.ts` — \"produces same JSON output as audit --fix --json\"\n    20→\n    21→### AC #5: Harness not initialized error matches audit behavior\n    22→- **Verified:** Same `executeAudit()` handler produces identical error.\n    23→- **Test:** `onboard.test.ts` — \"exits with fail when harness not initialized\", \"exits with JSON fail when not initialized with --json\"\n    24→\n    25→### AC #6: `codeharness onboard scan` prints deprecation warning then runs audit\n    26→- **Verified:** `scan` subcommand calls `warn()` with deprecation message then calls `executeAudit()`.\n    27→- **Test:** `onboard.test.ts` — \"prints deprecation warning and runs audit\", \"prints deprecation warning even with 