{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SeykkPhi15u7dNZcgkedBH","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. All clean. Let me do a final summary of what was done and what remains.\n\n---\n\n## Code Review Summary: Story 3.3 Onboard Alias\n\n**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-3-onboard-alias.md`\n**Status:** Updated to `verifying`\n\n### Fixes Applied\n\n1. **HIGH: Unsafe double type assertion** (`audit-action.ts` line 86) -- Replaced `formatAuditJson(result.data) as unknown as Record<string, unknown>` with spread operator `{ ...formatAuditJson(result.data) }`. The double-cast through `unknown` bypassed TypeScript's type system entirely.\n\n2. **MEDIUM: Dead branch / unreachable guard** (`audit-action.ts` line 101) -- The `else if (fixStories && !fixStories.success)` had a redundant truthiness check on `fixStories` that could never be false at that point in the control flow (guaranteed assigned when `gapCount > 0`). Simplified to `else` with `fixStories!` non-null assertions to match the invariant.\n\n3. **MEDIUM: NFR9 violation** (`onboard.test.ts` was 325 lines, limit is 300) -- Compacted test setup helpers, removed blank lines, used shared fixtures. Reduced from 325 to 230 lines.\n\n4. **MEDIUM: Branch coverage gap** (`audit-action.ts` 95.83% branch coverage) -- Added test for `s.skipped === true` path in JSON fix output (line 96). Added test for fix generation failure in JSON mode via onboard path. Combined with the dead-branch fix, achieved 100% branch coverage.\n\n### Verification Results\n\n- Build: tsup compiles successfully\n- Tests: 108 files, 2783 tests, 0 failures, 0 regressions\n- Coverage: 96.97% overall, all 119 files above 80% per-file floor\n- Target files: audit-action.ts, audit.ts, onboard.ts all at 100% (statements, branches, functions, lines)\n- NFR9: all files under 300 lines (119, 25, 40, 230 respectively)\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: Unsafe double type assertion in `audit-action.ts:86` -- `as unknown as Record<string, unknown>` bypasses type safety. Fixed with spread operator.\n- MEDIUM: Unreachable branch guard in `audit-action.ts:101` -- `fixStories &&` guard was always true at that point. Simplified to plain `else`.\n- MEDIUM: `onboard.test.ts` at 325 lines exceeded NFR9 300-line limit. Compacted to 230 lines.\n- MEDIUM: Branch coverage at 95.83% -- missing test for `skipped: true` path. Added test, now 100%.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- `console.log(line)` at `audit-action.ts:111` technically violates the story's \"Do NOT use console.log directly\" dev note, but this is the established pattern across the codebase (status.ts, query.ts, validate.ts, retry.ts all do the same). The `output.ts` utilities add `[OK]`/`[FAIL]` prefixes unsuitable for raw audit report lines. Would need a new `raw()` output utility to fix properly. Tech debt.\n- `formatAuditJson()` in `report.ts` is a pass-through (`return result`) -- no-op function. Exists for symmetry with `formatAuditHuman()` but adds no value. Minor tech debt.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None for story scope. All changed files at 100% coverage, all 119 project files above 80% floor, overall 96.97%.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The non-null assertions (`fixStories!`) on lines 91-103 are safe given the control flow but make the code slightly fragile to future refactoring. A restructuring that moves JSON formatting into the fix-handling block would eliminate the need for these assertions. Not blocking.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7eda61b04ce84232 (use SendMessage with to: 'a7eda61b04ce84232' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 71467\ntool_uses: 47\nduration_ms: 273454</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c9a200e-72ec-477b-8ec4-6d2e01a30422","uuid":"88af164b-153a-49ec-8bf9-17519e3f04c3","timestamp":"2026-03